name: Life in the Internet Age
description: Let's discuss how technology is changing the way we live
reason: Our world is rapidly changing thanks to new technology, and the vocabulary needed to discuss modern life is evolving almost daily. In this course you will learn the most up-to-date terminology from expertly crafted lessons as well from your native-speaking tutor.
purpose: You will learn vocabulary related to timely topics like remote work, artificial intelligence, online privacy, and more. In addition to discussion questions, you will practice intermediate level speaking tasks such as using data to describe trends.

name: Basic Conversation Topics
description: Gain confidence speaking about familiar topics
reason: It can be intimidating to speak with a foreigner, no matter how much grammar and vocabulary you've mastered. If you have basic knowledge of English but have not spent much time speaking, this course will help you ease into your first English conversations.
purpose: This course covers vocabulary at the CEFR A2 level. You will build confidence while learning to speak about a variety of common, everyday topics. In addition, you will build implicit grammar knowledge as your tutor models correct answers and corrects your mistakes.

topics.name: Having Fun in Your Free Time

name: Intermediate Conversation Topics
description: Express your ideas and opinions
reason: Looking for some variety in your lesson topics? Immerse yourself in English discussion with this set of engaging topics.
purpose: This course covers vocabulary at the CEFR B1-B2 levels. You will work on improving fluency and comprehension by discussing a variety of topics. In addition, you will receive corrections from a native English speaker to help improve your grammatical accuracy.

name: Advanced Conversation Topics
description: Explore complex topics relevant to modern life
reason: Challenge yourself with new topics to expand you vocabulary and increase your comfort with the English language.
purpose: This course covers vocabulary at the CEFR C1-C2 levels. You will work on gaining fluency by speaking at length about a wide array of topics. In addition, you will receive corrections from a native English speaker to help improve coherence and grammatical accuracy.

name: Caring for Our Planet
description: Let's discuss our relationship as humans with our planet, Earth
reason: As climate change and environmentalism become increasingly global issues, this topic appears often in international news and is relevant to many international industries.
purpose: This course covers intermediate level vocabulary related to sustainability and environmental science. In addition, you will complete technical tasks such as describing charts, analyzing data, and making estimations.

name: Healthy Mind, Healthy Body
description: Let's discuss the many aspects of living a long, happy life
purpose: Discuss topics related to physical, mental, and emotional health. Learn about other cultures along the way in friendly conversations with tutors.

name: Business English
description: The English you need for your work and career
reason: Understanding business culture and customs is just as important as learning traditional business-related vocabulary. With Cambly's Business English course, you have the chance to learn from expertly-crafted lessons as well as from your tutor's personal experiences.
purpose: This course covers the most common vocabulary and grammatical structures needed to do business in English. The course focuses on simulating real-life business situations to build professional communicative competency. You will also learn idioms being used in English-speaking offices across the globe.

name: IELTS Speaking Part 1
description: Practice answering Part 1 questions from past years' IELTS exams
reason: Feeling confident answering Part 1 questions will help you get off to a strong start on your IELTS speaking exam.
purpose: You'll practice giving strong answers in Part 1, with tips and tricks recommended by real IELTS examiners.

name: IELTS Speaking Part 2
description: Practice answering Part 2 questions from past years' IELTS exams
reason: Comfort with speaking on your own for an extended period of time will help you ace Part 2 of the IELTS speaking exam.
purpose: You'll practice speaking at length for Part 2, with tips and tricks recommended by real IELTS examiners.

name: IELTS Speaking Part 3
description: Practice answering Part 3 questions from past years' IELTS exams
reason: Answering open-ended questions asked by a native speaker is the best way to simulate Part 3 of the IELTS speaking exam.
purpose: You'll practice answering Part 3 questions from previous years' exams, with tips and tricks recommended by real IELTS examiners.

name: IELTS Speaking Mock Tests
description: Prepare for IELTS Speaking with exams from previous years
reason: The best way to prepare for IELTS? Simulate the full experience with real IELTS questions and get feedback on your mistakes from a native speaker.
purpose: You'll gain familiarity with the most commonly asked IELTS Speaking questions, as well as the most frequent questions from recent years.

name: English Conversation 101
description: Approachable lessons for absolute beginners
reason: Are you worried you are not ready to speak English with a native speaker? We created this course to provide all the guidance you need to shed that fear and start speaking today!
purpose: We'll start simple by learning how to introduce yourself and exchange greetings. By the last lesson, you'll have the necessary skills to continue practicing and improving your conversational English on Cambly.

topics.name: Let's See What You Can Do!

name: Movies and Television
description: Let's discuss our preferences and habits surrounding movies and television shows
reason: Movies and television shows are common topics of conversation among friends and coworkers. In this course, you will practice discussing the movies and television shows you've seen and sharing your opinions about them.
purpose: You will learn vocabulary related to movies and television.  In addition, you will practice the grammatical structures that help you tell a story, and share and explain your likes and dislikes.

name: Advanced Business English
description: Advanced English for your work and career
reason: Cambly's Advanced Business English course will help you excel in your workplace by teaching you the language skills you need to discuss specialized topics in business.
purpose: This course covers 14 specialized topics in business such as marketing, e-commerce, and outsourcing. You will learn the vocabulary and grammatical structures needed to participate in discussions about each topic. The course focuses on simulating real-life business situations to build professional communicative competency. You will also learn to confidently talk about your own professional experiences and expertise.

name: TOEFL Speaking Practice
description: Prepare for TOEFL speaking with practice test questions modeled on real TOEFL exams
reason: The best way to prepare for TOEFL speaking? Learn about each question type, and then simulate the full experience with practice questions, all while getting feedback from an expert English speaker.
purpose: This course will introduce you to the four question types on the newest version of the TOEFL speaking exam. You'll gain familiarity with the format of each question, and gain confidence as you respond to exclusive practice questions specially designed to help you master TOEFL speaking.

name: Workshop: Practicing Presentations
description: Practice an upcoming presentation or speech
reason: Giving speeches or presentations can be nerve-wracking, especially in a second language. This course will help you feel comfortable and confident. You will practice your speech multiple times and get feedback from an expert English speaker.
purpose: You will receive valuable feedback on your presentation or speech in areas such as pronunciation, pacing, and grammar.

name: Workshop: Practicing Job Interviews
description: Practice for job interviews in English
reason: Job interviews can be stressful, especially in a second language. This course will give you confidence in your interviewing skills. Your expert tutor will give you valuable feedback as you practice using English to answer questions about your skills, experiences, and qualifications.
purpose: You will receive feedback from an expert English speaker on areas such as pronunciation, clarity, and grammar.

name: Raising Children
description: Let's discuss raising children and practice using English for common parenting situations
reason: Talking to other parents, friends, and family about family life is an important part of socializing in any language.
purpose: In this course, you will become familiar with the vocabulary of common topics related to raising children in the modern world. In addition, you will role play parenting situations such as talking to a doctor about your childs health and booking a babysitter.

topics.name: The Challenges and Joys of Parenting

name: The Exciting World of Startups
description: Specialized topics in professional English: Startups
reason: Startups are an exciting part of the business world. They sometimes fail, but when they succeed, they can change the world. This course will teach you the language skills you need to discuss startups, whether you are a student, a professional, or simply interested in this innovative part of the modern business landscape.
purpose: In this course, you will learn the unique vocabulary of startups, from "hackathon" to "angel investors" to "incubators". You will also practice advanced English grammar points all while getting practice and feedback with your expert English tutor.

name: Academic English
description: The English you need for school and research
reason: The English used in academic settings, such as textbooks and lectures, is more complex and specialized than conversational English. This course was designed based on research that identifies the most important features of academic English in order to help you speak with confidence in a variety of academic settings.
purpose: In this course, each lesson is focused on an academic language function, such as explaining cause and effect, describing ideas, or talking about data, charts and numbers. You'll learn critical academic vocabulary that accompanies each function. You'll also practice advanced grammar points that are common in academic language.

name: English Conversation 102
description: Even more approachable lessons for absolute beginners
purpose: Continue to develop your ability have simple conversations in English! This course has carefully structured lessons to help you build confidence when talking about topics such as the weather and hobbies. You'll also practice catching up with friends and telling stories. This course builds on the topics covered in English Conversation 101.

topics.name: What Do You Want to Learn?

name: Introduction to Public Speaking
description: Learn the basics of public speaking
reason: Public speaking is an important part of many jobs. This course will help you gain the confidence you need to speak in front of an audience in a variety of business situations such as leading a meeting, giving a status report, and making a sale.
purpose: This course covers important presentation skills such as articulating clearly, keeping your audience interested, and describing charts and graphs. You will practice useful grammar for each skill, along with professional vocabulary.

name: The Olympics
description: Lets practice talking about the Olympics, the biggest sports festival on earth!
reason: The Olympics is a wonderful celebration of sportsmanship and global cooperation, and a common topic of conversation for people all over the world! Practice using English to talk about interesting topics like Olympic host cities and differences between the Ancient and Modern Olympics.
purpose: In this course, youll learn advanced-level vocabulary and grammar and practice talking about data while reading charts and graphs. You'll also complete fun and creative tasks such as role-playing as an Olympic athlete and discussing the future of the Olympics with new technology.

name: Intermediate Conversation Topics Part 2
description: More practice expressing your ideas and opinions in English
reason: Continue to develop your conversational English with more intermediate conversation topics!
purpose: In this course, you'll practice discussing topics such as money, exercise and diet, and social media. At the same time, you'll learn vocabulary at the B1-B2 level.
